    />
    <p><strong>Key specs:</strong> Burr grinder · single-cup to 12-cup output · Beans+Ground mode · thermal carafe format.</p>
    <p><strong>Why it wins this slot:</strong> It is the strongest upgrade path if your main complaint is muddy flavor from blade-based one-cup machines.</p>
    <p><strong>Retention/static behavior:</strong> Moderate retention in the burr chamber; weekly brush-out sharply improves repeatability.</p>
    <p><CtaButton href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B00VGGVQCI" external>Check price on Amazon</CtaButton></p>

    <h3>3) Gevi Single Serve (K-Cup + Ground) — Best for low-maintenance routines</h3>
    <p><strong>Verdict:</strong> Buy this if easy cleanup and flexible brew modes matter more than chasing maximum cup nuance.</p>
